The Africa Union And The World Bank Are Among Institutions That Have Agreed To Support SMEs In The Upcoming Dubai 2020 Expo Slated Next Month. Kenyan Entrepreneurs Especially Those In The Micro, Small And Medium Enterprises Have Been Encouraged To Attend The Expo And Showcase Their Different Products The Uae Has Continuously Preferred Kenya As Its Trading Hub In Africa And Has Guaranteed A 2 Year Extension To Kenyans Showcasing Their Products At The Expo. The Expo Is Set To Be Attended By Over 180 Nations With Over 20 Million Attendees. Kenyan Exhibitors Will Also Get Free Showcase Stalls At The Expo.